# Model Policy

## Default: composer-2 (fast)
Use for ALL execution unless explicitly marked otherwise.
Cheap, fast, sufficient for atomic tasks.

## Opus 4.6 (high thinking): Planner ONLY
The planner is the single point where deep reasoning pays off.
A wrong DAG = cascading waste across all downstream agents.

## Allocation

| Agent        | Model                    | Why                                         |
|-------------|--------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Planner     | claude-4.6-opus (think)  | DAG correctness, dependency reasoning, risk |
| Splitter    | composer-2 (fast)        | Pattern-matching on clear criteria          |
| Executor    | composer-2 (fast)        | Atomic implementation, runs most often      |
| Reviewer    | composer-2 (fast)        | Checklist validation against DoD            |
| Orchestrator| composer-2 (fast)        | Mechanical coordination                     |

## Cost Rationale
- Executor runs ~70% of all agent invocations → must be cheapest
- Planner runs ~5% of invocations → opus cost is negligible at scale
- One bad DAG costs more than 100 opus calls (rework, failed specs, wasted executor runs)

## Escalation
If reviewer detects an architectural violation or repeated failures:
→ Escalate to planner (opus) for re-planning
→ Never throw more executor runs at a structural problem
